{{intranslation}}
{{nihongo|'''Taira Hara'''|<U+306F><U+3089> <U+305F><U+3044><U+3089>|Hara Taira|[[8 March]] [[1943]] - [[10 November]] [[2006]]}} is a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] [[mangaka|manga artist]] and [[tarento]] born in [[Tosayamada, K<U+014D>chi|Tosayamada]] (now part of [[Kami, K<U+014D>chi|Kami]]), [[K<U+014D>chi Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. He was a long-time resident of [[Koishikawa]], [[Bunky<U+014D>, Tokyo|Bunky<U+014D>]], [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]. 

==History==
Hara was the oldest son, though he had an older sister. His father died of [[tuberculosis]] before he was born. 

Hara died of [[Liver tumor|liver cancer]] on [[10 November]] [[2006]] at a hospital in [[Fujimi, Saitama|Fujimi]], [[Saitama Prefecture]]. 


